  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nCurrent default network name is hard-coded to `development`, which may collide with the naming convention for the homologous remote environment. It would be nice to be able to override this default, maybe by placing a `defaultNetwork` option in `truffle.js` file.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nDeclare a `development` network configuration in the `truffle.js` file and run `truffle console`. \r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTry to take the default network name from `truffle.js` file or use `development` if there is none.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nTruffle uses `development` network whenever the `--network` option is not specified.",
